	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The solution is very easy then: make games for the SNES but restrict your palette to only the colors that the Genesis can produce, except for the ones that "just not there".
<br />
<br />This may sound like a joke, but if you think about it it really makes sense. If you reduce your options on purpose, it gets easier to pick the initial palettes, and then you fine tune the ones that feel off.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


