	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />RPG palette?
<br />
<br />I think the ideal color space for games would be HSY, (hue, saturation, luminance) but I don't know where I can get one.
<br />
<br />With RGB palettes, I think 4096 colors is the perfect balance between too little and too much.  I always thought the SNES's 32000 colors was overkill for the type of graphics that you usually saw on the SNES.  The CPS2 only had 4096 colors and nobody ever complained about it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


