	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A problem with HSL is that, despite its friendliness to art designers, it's not well suited for use at runtime in any environment that has to implement gel (colored lighting) or translucency. So GIMP has a couple color pickers that display the color in HSL and then convert it to RGB after the user clicks OK.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


